INSERT INTO `staff` VALUES (1,'James','Tayler','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/james-tayler.jpg','','<p>James initially worked as an engineer on nuclear submarines in the Royal Navy before retraining as a navy helicopter pilot. After nearly 30 years flying a variety of military aircraft for the British and New Zealand navies, he moved to the civilian EMS world initially flying the Sikorsky S76 before joining ARHT in 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, James likes to ride his motorbike (carefully). In the winter he enjoys skiing and during the warmer weather spending time on the water, fishing, paddleboarding and kayaking.</p>','A',7,''),(2,'Roger','Hortop','Flight Operations Manager / Chief Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/roger-hortop.jpg','','<p>Roger joined ARHT in July 2014, having&nbsp;previously worked with Westpac Rescue helicopter from 2000 &ndash; 2005</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Roger has flown extensively in the Northern Territory, Queensland and Western Australia from cattle/buffalo mustering, marine pilot transfers, charter and oil rig support. Roger has over 10 years experience in Flight operations for EMS, Charter and Police operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His interests include sailing, traveling, cooking and enjoying a good red wine with his wife Sharon, as well as being a father of two daughters, Zoe and Emily.</p>','A',1,'1'),(3,'Rob','Arrowsmith','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/rob-arrowsmith.jpg','','<p>Rob&nbsp;joined ARHT in 2010, after 13 years in the NZ Air Force flying helicopters throughout NZ, East Timor, New Caledonia and Fiji.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Military flying had many exciting moments for him, but the most rewarding were the infrequent medical / SAR jobs, which&nbsp;he gets to do daily at ARHT.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the sun is shining, Rob is able to watch a lot of what the clinicians do for&nbsp;the patients &ndash; the complexity of the scenes that they&rsquo;re working within while keeping a sharp mind and remaining compassionate is something he finds awe inspiring.&nbsp;When the weather is bad, he feels fortunate to have generous supporters which allow the crew to maintain the ability to fly through the weather on instruments only, a capability&nbsp;he is very&nbsp;passionate about. Rob says the only downside of the job is getting around the region so quickly by chopper, only to then get in your car and slowly crawl through the traffic afterwards!</p>','A',3,''),(4,'Paul','Robinson','Pilot / Training Manager','','','','','/library/pilots/paul-robinson.jpg','','<p>Paul joined ARHT in 2011.&nbsp; He has a background in EMS, flying an S76 in Northland and working on Police operations around Auckland.&nbsp; He is a Flight Instructor, NVG Instructor and one of our ARHT Flight Examiners.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paul looks after the Training Department, which involves making sure everyone is up to speed &ndash; a task he says is made easier by the high calibre of our crew! He enjoys the challenge of&nbsp;the job and considers it a privilege to work at ARHT.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paul is happily married with twin teenage daughters. He&nbsp;enjoys time off when he can get it.</p>','A',5,''),(5,'Johnny','Stanton','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/johnny-stanton.jpg','','<p>Johnny joined ARHT from the Royal New Zealand Navy, where he flew and instructed on the Seasprite. The highlight of his military career was anti-piracy and counter-narcotic operations off the Horn of Africa and Somalia when on exchange with the Royal Navy flying the Lynx.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New to EMS, Johnny enjoys the real difference each mission can make to our patients.&nbsp; Outside work, he enjoys racket sports, the TV programme &#39;Suits&#39;, and hanging out with his family.</p>','A',6,''),(6,'James','Dearman','HEMS Doctor','','','','','','','<p>James joined ARHT in August 2016 after 7 years as a doctor in the UK. He is undertaking a 1 year fellowship in Helicopter Emergency Medicine and Emergency Medicine and will return to the UK to finish his medical training in the Oxford deanery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>James has really enjoyed working with the team and loves the rewards and challenges presented by Pre-hospital care, bringing life-saving treatments to patients before they reach hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside work, James enjoys exploring this beautiful country with his wife, Emma - tramping, scuba diving, sketching, fishing and photography. He&rsquo;s already planning his next trip back!</p>','D',0,''),(7,'Brett','Gerrard','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-brett-gerrard.jpg','','<p>Brett has worked as a HEMS Emergency Doctor in Auckland since 2012. Originally from Dunedin, he has worked in Emergency and Aviation Medicine around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brett&#39;s&nbsp;love of the wild outdoors has seen him travel as an Expedition Doctor to the atolls of Tahiti, the summit of Mt Kilimanjaro and the deserts of Namibia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is currently completing a Masters of Aviation Medicine and while still supporting the mighty Highlanders, is extremely happy to be calling Auckland home.</p>','A',5,''),(8,'Ula','Heywood','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-ula-heywood.jpg','','<p>Ula (pronounced You-la)&nbsp;moved to New Zealand from the UK and loves being able to work in a team of skilled professionals, who can bring order and calm to a scene of fear, pain and chaos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ula says it is great to turn that around and stabilise a sick patient, especially, if they are lucky enough,&nbsp;&nbsp;to see them make a good recovery. She says that is the best reward for doing this job, alongside the laughter and camaraderie that comes from working with great people.</p>','A',7,''),(9,'Christopher','Denny','Medical Director of Auckland HEMS','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-chris-denny.jpg','','<p>Chris joined the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust in September 2011 to serve as the inaugural Auckland Helicopter Emergency Medical Services (HEMS) Medical Director. He says it is a privilege to work with our ARHT team to develop a clinical service at the vanguard of early, safe, optimal patient care.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to moving to New Zealand, Chris worked in Toronto, Ontario, Canada as an academic Emergency Physician, Trauma Team Leader, Transport Medicine Physician and Urban Search and Rescue Team Doctor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chris also works as a Senior Medical Officer in Emergency Medicine at the Auckland City Hospital, and as a Clinical Team Leader for the New Zealand Medical Assistance Team. Chris and his family are grateful to live in the beautiful region of Auckland.</p>','A',1,''),(10,'Dean','Bunbury','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-dean-bunbury.jpg','','<p>Dean&#39;s&nbsp;association with the Westpac Rescue helicopter began through Surf Life Saving in the late 1980&rsquo;s.&nbsp; Since that time,&nbsp;he has worked for a variety of search and rescue, pre-hospital and aeromedical organisations in a number of countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Originally from Auckland,&nbsp;Dean has&nbsp;now returned home and works predominantly as a Paediatric Anaesthetist at Middlemore Hospital (CMDHB) and with HEMS.</p>','A',11,''),(11,'Heidi','Baker','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-heidi-baker.jpg','','<p>Heidi joined the ARHT HEMS team in June 2015.&nbsp; She works in dual consultant roles at Auckland Hospital in Adult Emergency and Paediatric Emergency Medicine at Starship.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mum to three children and hailing from a rural background,&nbsp;Heidi has always recognized the need for pre-hospital care in isolated areas for both adults and children.&nbsp; In her&nbsp;days off&nbsp;she loves to spend time exploring the outdoors with her family, or running mountain trails.</p>','A',2,''),(12,'Brendan','Wood','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-brendan-wood.jpg','','<p>Brendan arrived in New Zealand&nbsp;from Canada to do his fellowship in Pre-Hospital Medicine and has been with ARHT since 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is in-training to be a specialist in Emergency Medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brendan enjoys working with ARHT because of the great teamwork and innovative approach to pre-hospital medicine. Outside of work he likes to explore the mountains and beaches of New Zealand.</p>','D',11,''),(13,'Emma','Batistich','HEMS Doctor (Acting HEMS Education Lead)','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-emma-batistich-headshot.jpg','','<p>Emma joined&nbsp;ARHT in November 2015 as a HEMS doctor. She also works as an Emergency Medicine Specialist at Auckland City&nbsp;Hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Emma loves working with the ARHT team and all the challenges of taking the resuscitation room to the beach/roadside/paddock.&nbsp;Outside of work she&nbsp;enjoys travel adventures,&nbsp;cycling, crossfit and SCUBA&nbsp;diving when feeling energetic, and knitting/Netflix when some blobbing is needed.&nbsp;</p>','A',3,''),(14,'Alana','Harper','FACEM (HEMS Lead Safety, Quality and Training)','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-alana-harper.jpg','','<p>Alana is an Emergency Medicine Specialist at Auckland City Hospital. She has been a HEMS Doctor with the ARHT since 2011, and loves being able to provide critical-care level medicine outside of the hospital, and the variety of work this job brings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of medicine, Alana&nbsp;is mum to a young family.</p>','A',6,''),(15,'Paul','Blakemore','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-paul-blakemore.jpg','','<p>Paul arrived in Invercargill from the UK in 2008 and finished his emergency medicine training in Auckland, working as an ARHT HEMS Fellow in 2015.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite moving to Tauranga to take on a role as their trauma lead in the emergency department, he continues to fly with the Trust twice a month.&nbsp; When not traveling between both cities, he loves kayak fishing, cooking curries and spending time with his little kiwi daughter.</p>','A',4,''),(16,'Nicholas','Longley','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-nicholas-longley.jpg','','<p>Nick joined ARHT as a HEMS Doctor in 2016 and also works as an Emergency Medicine Physician in the Auckland region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to returning to Auckland in 2011, Nick worked and lived in the UK and Australia for many years. His spare time is spent with his wife, enjoying watching&nbsp;their young son Sebastian grow, explore and develop.</p>','A',9,''),(17,'Tony','Smith','HEMS Doctor and Medical Director, St Johns','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-tony-smith.jpg','','<p>Tony joined ARHT in 2011 as one of the HEMS doctors. He is also an Intensive Care Medicine Specialist at Auckland City Hospital and is the Medical Director for St John Ambulance in New Zealand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tony has been with the HEMS team since it began and is very passionate about improving emergency care to people throughout New Zealand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Married with two adult daughters, Tony is keen on cycling, fishing and gardening during the few periods he is not at work.</p>','A',10,''),(18,'Emily','Junck','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-emily-junck.jpg','','<p>Emily joined ARHT in 2016 from the United States as a rescue doctor and helicopter EMS fellow. She trained in Emergency Medicine in Seattle and was working in a small hospital in Alaska prior to coming to New Zealand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Emily&#39;s&nbsp;goal is to become an EMS medical director upon returning to the U.S., in addition to continuing her work in Alaska.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, she enjoys salsa dancing, running, cycling, hiking, and exploring new places.</p>','A',8,''),(19,'Casey','Drum','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/casey-drum.jpg','','<p>Casey joined ARHT in May 2016, after&nbsp;seven years&nbsp;at St John Ambulance.&nbsp;Ten years&nbsp;prior to that he was&nbsp;leading white water expedition rafting trips internationally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Casey enjoys the challenge of combining rescue and pre-hospital medicine.&nbsp;On his days off&nbsp;he loves spending time with his two sons and his&nbsp;wife at the beach or in the caravan. Other&nbsp;interests include making furniture, beekeeping and surfing.</p>','A',7,''),(20,'Russell (Rusty)','Clark','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/rusty-clark.jpg','','<p>Rusty has worked at the ARHT for the last four years, and been an Intensive Care Paramedic for 11 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He loves the&nbsp;challenges and rewarding nature of the pre-hospital environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rusty enjoys&nbsp;spending his spare time with his soulmate, Kateshe, and their two boys.&nbsp;</p>','A',3,''),(21,'Mark (Tinny)','Cannell','Chief Crewman','','','','','/library/crewmen/mark-cannell.jpg','','<p>Tinny joined ARHT in 2004 as a Crewman. Prior to this he served with the NZ Airforce for 14 years, conducting operations in various theatres.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On his days off, Tinny enjoys the outdoors, especially fishing with his daughter, Charlea.</p>','A',1,''),(22,'Ati','Wynyard','Crewman','','','','','/library/crewmen/ati-wynyard.jpg','','<p>Ati joined ARHT in 2010 employed as a casual Crewman. He became full time in 2012. Previous to that he worked for 23 years in the Royal New Zealand Navy as a Helicopter Crewman Instructor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ati enjoys all sports, music, fishing and camping and most of his spare time is taken up by coaching kids sports and keeping up with a busy lifestyle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ati says the best part about&nbsp;his job is meeting up with past patients&nbsp;he has rescued and answering their questions&nbsp;about what&nbsp;happened on the day.</p>','A',7,''),(23,'Marcel','Driessen','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/marcel-driessen.jpg','','<p>Marcel&rsquo;s connection with the ARHT began in the mid 1990&rsquo;s on a casual / informal basis well before full-time medical crewing. Since the early 2000&#39;s he has worked in a more permanent role for the Trust.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Marcel&#39;s background is with St John initially as a volunteer in Tairua and then eventually as an Intensive Care Paramedic in Auckland in the mid 1990&#39;s. For Marcel, the never knowing - where, when and what the challenges of the job will be on a daily basis (from helping to deliver a baby in the helicopter to providing lifesaving treatment for a car crash or medical patient or rescuing a tramper out of the bush) is what he thrives on. The camaraderie between the crews and working within high pressure environments also add to&nbsp;his satisfaction of helping others out in their time of need.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a &lsquo;Westie&rsquo;,&nbsp;Marcel enjoys the various opportunities that the Waitakere bush and West Coast beaches offer.</p>','A',6,''),(24,'Rob','Anderson','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/rob-anderson.jpg','','<p>Rob has been employed with ARHT since 2009.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has&nbsp;flown in Auckland and overseas, including Canada and the Arctic tundra, as well as&nbsp;Fiji.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He enjoys spending his spare time with his wife and young boy.</p>','A',2,''),(25,'Aaron','Knight','Crewman / Co-Pilot','','','','','/library/crewmen/aaron-knight.jpg','','<p>Aaron joined ARHT in 2015.&nbsp;He has always had a huge passion for flying from a young age. He gained his CPL(H) in 2008,&nbsp; completed CPL(A) in 2015 and has a single pilot IFR rating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aaron has flown helicopters in far north Queensland Australia in the Torres Straits, on extensive over water operations and flown out of a remote community in northern BC Canada, on Oil and Gas support, as well as wild animal tracking and recovery.</p>','A',3,''),(26,'Simon','Owen','Crewman / Co-Pilot','','','','','/library/crewmen/simon-owen.jpg','','<p>Simon joined ARHT in April 2016 as a Crewman/Co-Pilot.&nbsp;Before this, he spent the last&nbsp;four years as a helicopter pilot in Kakadu National Park, Northern Territory, Australia, predominantly conducting a variety of land management tasks, including aerial prescribed burning, firefighting, feral animal control and flora surveys.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simon&rsquo;s goal was always to become an EMS helicopter pilot and he enjoys the combination of the practical and procedural aspect of the role. Outside work, he enjoys bush and beach walks with his wife. Sophie, and cruising on his motorbike.</p>','A',4,''),(27,'Russell','Clarke','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/russell-clarke.jpg','','<p>Russell joined ARHT in 2009.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He previously worked in the New Zealand Air Force, where he served as a paramedic for 20 years.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>','A',4,'1'),(28,'Dave','Walley','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/davewalley.jpg','','<p>Dave learnt to fly in&nbsp; the RAF in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has flown in the North Sea, Borneo, Dubai, the Falklands, Kenya, and for Greenpeace in Antarctic, Arctic, Tasman and Pacific arenas.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dave is also NZ&#39;s only qualified Commercial Airship Pilot, flew a Boeing 737 for Air NZ and was a Civil Aviation Authority Inspector.&nbsp; Dave is also the designated CAA examiner for several of New Zealand&rsquo;s Rescue Helicopter Trusts.&nbsp;</p>','H',8,''),(29,'Ross','Aitken','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/ross-aitken.jpg','','<p>Ross has worked in the ambulance service for 14 years and for ARHT for&nbsp;4 years. He loves working in this industry and says that combining medicine&nbsp;with rescue work is what makes this people-centred job so&nbsp;fantastic.</p>','A',2,''),(30,'Rob','Gemmell','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/rob-gemmell-2.jpg','','<p>Rob has been an ambulance Paramedic for 18 years and has been flying in EMS helicopters for the last 10 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has been serving the greater Auckland region with the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust for the past 7 years and says the most rewarding part of his career&nbsp;is putting the patient first and engaging in continual innovation.</p>','A',9,''),(31,'Karl','Taylor','Chief Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/karl-taylor.jpg','','','H',1,'1'),(32,'Chris (Deacs)','Deacon','Intensive Care Paramedic','','','','','/library/paramedics/chris-deacon.jpg','','<p>&#39;Deacs&#39; has been on the ARHT team since 1997 and worked as an ambulance officer for St John beforehand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chris was recognised in June 2012 as having completed&nbsp;2,000 rescue missions.</p>','H',5,''),(33,'John (Winnie)','Skirrow','Crewman','','','','','/library/crewmen/john-skirrow.jpg','','<p>Winnie started working on the Westpac Rescue Helicopter as a volunteer back in 1986. He became a fulltime crewman in 1994 and is one of our most long-standing staff members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has participated in over&nbsp;2,000 rescue missions&nbsp;and was recognised for this achievement in 2009.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Winnie&nbsp;has been a keen surfer for many years and is a member of the Muriwai surf club.&nbsp;</p>','A',6,''),(34,'Murray','Bolton','Chairman','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/murraybolton.jpg','','<p>Murray has had extensive experience in a wide range of organisations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His experience includes:<br />\r\nPublic Accountant in NZ and UK for KPMG. Vice President in bank and finance for Citigroup in Canada, Mexico and USA. CEO of Rural Banking, Finance Corporation of New Zealand. CEO of Brierly Investments Ltd. New Zealand CEO of Skellerup Group Ltd. Private Investor for a diverse group of businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murray has also been on the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust Board of Trustees since 1990.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>','A',2,''),(35,'Bob','Parkinson','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/bob-parkinson2.jpg','','<p>Bob Parkinson is a company director and business consultant. He was a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants from 1970 until 2000, and a partner in an Auckland public accounting practice from 1975 to 1996.&nbsp; His past directorships included both publicly listed and private companies covering a diverse range of services, products and activities in New Zealand, Australia and Fiji.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bob&nbsp;has also had a long term involvement in the healthcare and medical sectors in which he continues to consult and hold directorships, as well as extensive involvement as a trustee and administrator in a wide range of trusts including charitable, medical research and education, and superannuation, family and investment trusts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bob held the position of CEO of the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust from 2007-2013.</p>','A',3,''),(36,'Michelle','Boag','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/michelleboag.jpg','','<p>Michelle Boag is a partner in Strategic Communications Consultancy Boag Allan Pirie, based in Auckland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMichelle has had a high profile career in public relations and politics,&nbsp; along with extensive involvement with a wide range of community, voluntary and professional associations. Her thirty-five year career includes working in Parliament for three National Party Leaders, managing public relations consultancies in Auckland and Wellington and senior management positions in the merchant banking and corporate world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe other Boards and Trusts on which Michelle has served as a Director Eden Park Trust (current), Auckland Cricket Association, Manu Samoa Rugby Ltd, Television New Zealand, Advertising Standards Complaints Board and Auckland Surf Lifesaving Association. Michelle is also a former President of the NZ National Party and of the Variety Club of New Zealand.</p>','A',5,''),(37,'Ken','Baguley','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/kenbaguley.jpg','','<p>Ken is a self-employed retired Accountant,&nbsp;married with three married children and six grandchildren.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ken served as an Auckland City councillor for the Hobson Ward from 2007 to 2010, where he was Chairman of the Transport Committee of the Auckland City Council.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ken has been an elected member of the Orakei Local Board of Auckland Council from 2011 to 2016, and a Trustee of the Eden Park Trust Board from 2012.&nbsp; He was chairman of the Auckland Rugby Football Union Board of Directors from 2001 to 2010, is a Life Member of Auckland Rugby Union and a Life Trustee for the Halberg Trust.</p>','A',5,''),(38,'John','McDougall','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/johnmcdougal.jpg','','<p>John McDougall is a specialist anaesthetist, having trained in both New Zealand and the United Kingdom. He is a Fellow of the Royal College of Anaesthetists and a Fellow of the Australian and New Zealand College of Anaesthetists. He was appointed a consultant anaesthetist to Green Lane Hospital in 1984 and has practised as an anaesthetist in both private and public sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John has been involved with the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust as a trustee since the early 1990&#39;s and prior to that with the original beach based Surf Life Saving helicopter. He organised the donor retrieval logistics for the cardiac transplant programme and has been involved in fixed wing ambulance services. His major focus over the past five years, in conjunction with ambulance services and physicians from the Emergency Department of Auckland District Hospital Board, has been the development of a paramedic / doctor model as the primary response team flying on ARHT rescue helicopters.</p>','A',4,''),(39,'Craig','Marshall','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/craigmarshall.jpg','','<p>Craig has been involved in the health sector in New Zealand over the past 25 years, in particular A&amp;E medicine and pathology services. Craig was previously CEO of Labtests, New Zealand&rsquo;s largest pathology laboratory, and has held senior management roles including: CEO of the White Cross Accident and Medical Group, GM of Southern Community Laboratories and CEO of Corporate Cabs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Craig is currently the CEO of Transaction Services Group.</p>','A',7,''),(40,'John','Hawkesby','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/hawkesby.jpg','','<p>Auckland-born former broadcaster John Hawkesby has lived on Waiheke Island since 2001.&nbsp; The father of three and grandfather of eleven splits his time between freelance writing for a variety of publications, MCing events, making after-dinner speeches and trying to expand his limited culinary experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nJohn has authored three books, &lsquo;Save The Last Dance for Me&rsquo; (1997), &lsquo;Vintage&rsquo; (2006) and &lsquo;Waiheke&hellip;An Island and its People&rsquo; (2013).&nbsp; He shares his home with wife, Joyce, a black Labrador called Georgie and copious rabbits that play havoc in his tiny vineyard. John enjoys good food, great wine and wonderful conversations and will go to extraordinary lengths to see Bob Dylan in concert.</p>','A',8,''),(41,'Stefan','Gabor','Intensive Care Paramedic / Clinical Educator','','','','','/library/paramedics/stefan-gabor.jpg','','<p>Stefan has a&nbsp;lifesaving background, joining Karekare Surf Lifesaving club when&nbsp;he was 15. Before joining the &#39;crazy ARHT crew&#39; he was employed by St John Ambulance Service as an Intensive Care Paramedic. This role he held for almost 20 years, where he performed a variety of duties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stefan has been a part of the ARHT team for eight years now, five as a part-time&nbsp;Intensive&nbsp;Care&nbsp;paramedic and three juggling that with&nbsp;his other role&nbsp;as Clinical Educator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is married&nbsp;with two young kids who keep him busy. When he is <em>allowed out</em> he loves to go fishing.</p>','A',8,''),(42,'Pippa','Wetzell','Ambassador','','','','','/library/paramedics/pippa.jpg','','<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">You&rsquo;ve seen her on the telly, most recently as presenter for Fair-Go and defender of Kiwis who have been left with very little options.&nbsp; Pippa Wetzell is a welcome addition to many of our homes, at least once a week, and she often does the odd stint on Seven Sharp and Breakfast too.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Pippa started working at TVNZ, one of our Corporate Sponsors, in the 90s, straight out of a Communications Degree. Working the overnight shift on the news desk, Pippa&rsquo;s roles included reporting and producing for Breakfast, Midday News, and Business. She was also a reporter for ONE News for five years, before taking up the presenting role on Breakfast.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">A busy mum as well, we are very fortunate to have Pippa on board as our Ambassador, flying the flag for her local Westpac Rescue Helicopter Service on top of her everyday life. Pippa tells us that supporting the service is an easy choice.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&ldquo;There are so many wonderful stories of people whose lives have been saved because of the Auckland and Coromandel Westpac Rescue Helicopter Service,&rdquo; she says, &ldquo;I&rsquo;m born and bred in Auckland and we holiday regularly in the Coromandel too. My family has spent a lot of time out and about exploring these beautiful regions and appreciate the incredible service the helicopter provides.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Pippa has another special connection with the Trust. &ldquo;My Dad was a surf lifesaver at Piha for many years starting in the 1960s. I understand the first rescue helicopter service was based out of Piha in the 70s and he would assist with rescues. It&rsquo;s something he&rsquo;s very proud of.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&ldquo;We Kiwis are an adventurous bunch,&rdquo; she tells us, &ldquo;We love to get out and explore our beautiful country and I wholeheartedly encourage that. It does mean though that you can find yourself out of the reach of facilities that you might need should an accident strike &ndash; you never know when you might need them.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Pippa&rsquo;s family have never needed to use the service themselves and she hopes they never will. &ldquo;Every time I see them flying, it gives me pause for thought. You realise there is a family somewhere who is going through significant angst.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Pippa&rsquo;s three kids think helicopters are &ldquo;fabulous&rdquo;. &ldquo;Ambulance helicopters (as they like to call them) are the ultimate though! They&rsquo;re keen to have a close up look, but look, if I&rsquo;m being totally honest, I hope they never have to get too close!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">We hope so too. From our crew to you, thank you Pippa for your generous support.</span></p>','A',1,''),(43,'Richard','Selby','Crewman / Co-Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/richard-selby.jpg','','<p>Richard joined ARHT in 2012 as crewman/co-pilot. With a background in sailing, originally qualified as a Naval Architect and having worked as a captain of super yachts for over 10 years, aviation arrived later in life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Working a part of a small dedicated team is certainly the highlight of&nbsp;his role with the rescue helicopter, and being involved across both the medical and aviation disciplines keeps the job exciting.</p>','A',5,''),(44,'Karl','Taylor','TO BE CONFIRMED','','','','','/library/paramedics/karl-taylor.jpg','','','D',0,''),(45,'Herby','Barnes','Safety Management Systems & Q.A. Manager','herby@arht.org.nz','021412477','09 9507212','','/library/support/herby-barnes.jpg','','<p>Herby came to the Trust from the Customs Department where he had served&nbsp;9 years as a Diver, Ship searcher and as a Crewman on their Marine response vessel HAWK II.&nbsp; He joined the Trust in 1995.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herby worked as Crew Chief&nbsp;on the helicopter&nbsp;until 2015, after which he took up a&nbsp;full-time role as&nbsp;Safety Management Systems &amp; Q.A. Manager,&nbsp;responsible for the Trusts Quality Assurance System, which involves&nbsp;conducting regular audits and monitoring procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herby is also qualified as a Winch Training Instructor, a Helicopter Underwater Escape Training Instructor (HUET) and is the lead Auditor for the organisation and has also participated in over&nbsp;2,000 rescues, being recognised for this achievement in 2009.</p>','A',8,'1'),(46,'John','Hooper','GM - Marketing & Fundraising','hoops@arht.org.nz','021 2748013','09 9507260','','/library/support/john-hoops-hooper.jpg','','<p>John (or Hoops as he is known by)&nbsp;heads the marketing&nbsp;and fundraising departments of the Trust and is responsible for raising the revenue required to maintain its essential rescue service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since joining the Trust in 1996, John has developed a corporate and community fundraising programme that has enabled ARHT to purchase and operate its own purpose-built BK117 B2 helicopters. He also builds and manages&nbsp;the VIP and sponsor partnerships. John has worked in the non-profit sector for over 25 years, managing fundraising projects for several air rescue trusts, The Royal N.Z. Plunket Society, New Zealand Police Association and many others.</p>','A',8,'1'),(47,'Greg','Barrow','Chief Executive Officer','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/greg-barrow.jpg','','<p>Greg Barrow comes from an extensive history in aviation as a pilot in both helicopters and fixed wing aircraft.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has been Chief Executive Officer of the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust since 2013.</p>','A',1,''),(48,'Lincoln','Davies','Communications Manager','lincolnd@arht.org.nz','','09 9507275','','/library/support/lincoln-new-profile-pic.jpg','','<p>Lincoln has worked for a number of New Zealand charities in communication roles. He started as a copywriter in the advertising industry, before making the leap to the not-for-profit sector in 1999.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lincoln finds great satisfaction in using his creative skills to support a good cause. He joined the Trust in 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, the father of two enjoys getting out amongst it all with his family and heading off on intrepid adventures with Kiwis to help others in need.</p>','A',2,'1'),(49,'Ken','Baguley','Trustee','','','','','/library/ceo-and-trustees/kenbaguley.jpg','','<p>Ken is a self-employed retired Accountant,&nbsp; married with three married children and six grandchildren .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ken served as an Auckland City councillor for the Hobson Ward from 2007 to 2010, where he was Chairman of the Transport Committee of the Auckland City Council.&nbsp;&nbsp;He has been an elected member of the Orakei Local Board of Auckland Council from 2011 to 2016 and a Trustee of the Eden Park Trust Board from 2012.&nbsp; He was chairman of the Auckland Rugby Football Union Board of Directors from 2001 to 2010, is a Life Member of Auckland Rugby Union and a Life Trustee for the Halberg Trust.</p>','D',0,''),(50,'Russell','Procter','Pilot','','','','','/library/pilots/russell-procter2.jpg','','<p>Russell is from across the ditch and has flown a variety of commercial operations in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2011 he saw the light and jumped to NZ, flying EMS on the S76 for another operation. Russell joined the Westpac Rescue team in 2015.&nbsp;</p>','A',4,'1'),(51,'Chris','Purdeu','Corporate Team member','chrisp@arht.org.nz','021 1356103','09 9507254','','/library/support/chris-purdeu.jpg','','<p>Chris joined the ARHT fundrasing team back in 1999, after completing a BA at university and making ends meet doing a variety of handy-man type jobs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now married with three kids, Chris just loves being a part of the ARHT team that helps save so many lives.</p>','A',14,'1'),(52,'Kerrie','Spicer','Planned Giving Manager','kerrie@arht.org.nz','021 2748458','09 9507222','','/library/support/kerrie.jpg','','<p>Kerrie started at the Trust in 2008 as PA to the&nbsp;CEO, a position she held for five years. After that time, Kerrie moved into two new part-time roles, Comms Adviser and Planned Giving Manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As from 1 July 2017, she transitioned to a full time Planned Giving Manager role. She enjoys this position, as she knows the importance of bequests to the rescue service and is humbled by the amount of people who leave a legacy&nbsp;to help&nbsp;others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In her spare time, Kerrie writes short plays and is currently writing a thriller novel set in Auckland.</p>','A',15,'1'),(53,'Michelle','Geange','Donation Support Manager','shellie@arht.org.nz','','09 9507203','','/library/support/michelle-geange-black-and-white-rs.jpg','','<p>Michelle (Shellie) has been with ARHT since 2001.&nbsp; Prior to that, she was juggling gaining her Diploma in Business Management and Diploma in Photography.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nShellie&nbsp;has been an integral part of our data processing team and has taken on a fundamental role within our new database system, ensuring that donations and statistical analysis is maintained accurately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','A',5,'1'),(54,'Missy','Taurere','Community Donation Support','database@arht.org.nz','','09 9507204','','/library/support/missy-taurere.jpg','','<p>Missy&nbsp;has been with the Trust since 2014.&nbsp;Juggling a number of different administration roles, she is responsible for looking after our Community Donors and the donations they make.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Formerly an airline boarding agent, Missy has loved jumping on board the rescue helicopter. &ldquo;I never thought I would work for ARHT. It&rsquo;s an awesome place and it&rsquo;s&nbsp;great seeing first-hand just how much wonderful support there is for the charity out there.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>','A',16,'1'),(55,'Katie','Tomlinson','Event Coordinator','events@arht.org.nz','','09 9507271','','/library/support/katie-tomlinson.jpg','','<p>Katie studied Event Management at AUT University and has worked in various event roles before joining ARHT in 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Katie&rsquo;s brother was once rescued by&nbsp;the helicopter&nbsp;crew one Christmas morning, so she knows just how important ARHT is.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In her spare time, Katie enjoys cooking,&nbsp;creating art, exploring the outdoors, playing touch rugby and planning her own music events.</p>','A',18,'1'),(56,'Dan','Coombe','Art Director / Designer','danc@arht.org.nz','','09 9507253','','/library/support/dan-coombe.jpg','','<p>Dan joined the Trust in late 2014 and produces all of our great looking artwork for direct mail, events and everything in between.</p>','A',1,'1'),(57,'Ros','Denton','Corporate Team member','rosd@arht.org.nz','021754515','09 9507273','','/library/support/ros-denton.jpg','','<p>Ros started with ARHT in 2011, bringing her passion for helping people and providing a great service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She is&nbsp;excited about being part of a great team&nbsp;which help&nbsp;deliver such an essential lifesaving service to everyone in the Auckland and Coromandel Regions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In&nbsp;her spare time, Ros and her husband like to escape to their bach in Whangamata, with&nbsp;the rest of the&nbsp;family and their dog, Lexi.</p>','A',3,'1'),(58,'Kim','Walker','Community Fundraising Manager','kimmyw@arht.org.nz','021 2748015','09 9507270','','/library/support/kim-walker.jpg','','<p>Kim joined ARHT in 2004 and has been involved in&nbsp;many different roles&nbsp;during this time. From running around teaching</p>\r\n\r\n<p>school students our Crew Fitness Test, through to conducting early morning boot camps for staff, and through to her&nbsp;most recent role&nbsp;of&nbsp;managing the Community Fundraising Team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kim loves the challenge of CrossFit, still gets excited about coming to work after all these years and feels like she does a good deed every day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She feels super proud to be part of the organisation and work alongside a wonderful bunch of people.</p>','A',20,'1'),(59,'Nigel','Hood','Corporate Team member','nigelh@arht.org.nz','02108175533','09 9507277','','/library/support/nigel-hood.jpg','','<p>Originally hailing from London, UK, Nigel spent&nbsp;seven and a half&nbsp;years in the RAF on a helicopter squadron. After leaving the RAF, Nigel worked as a photo manager on board cruise ships for several cruise lines, sailing throughout the Caribbean.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Returning back to the UK was not an option (after coming from such warm temperatures), so he moved out to Florida where he lived for 20 years. Here, he had his own commercial photography company and real estate brokerage, selling &nbsp;hotels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After arriving on the shores of New Zealand, Nigel got right&nbsp;into the kiwi culture, racing kayaks and Waka amas for a local team and training for his pilot licens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, you can often find him riding around this beautiful countryside on his motorcycle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nigel also volunteers with Coastguard Air Patrol, when not spending time with his two beautiful daughters, Hannah and Alexa.</p>','A',7,'1'),(60,'Phillip','Hedstrom','Corporate Team member','philh@arht.org.nz','0226822181','09 9507257','','/library/support/phil-hedstrom.jpg','','<p>Phillip started with the Trust in 2006 as part of a small Corporate Fundraising team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, Phillip enjoys fishing, golf and traveling to Asia and the Pacific Islands.</p>','A',6,'1'),(61,'Shaan','Hulena','Corporate Fundraising Manager','shaanh@arht.org.nz','0223550898','09 9507278','','/library/support/shaan-hulena.jpg','','<p>Shaan started working for the Trust in 2009, as part of the Corporate Fundraising Team. In 2013, he moved into his current role as the Corporate Fundraising Manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Shaan is not working with his team, securing the vital operational funding required by ARHT, you will find him either on the rugby field coaching&nbsp;two of his&nbsp;five kids&#39; rugby teams or, if time allows, he will be located outside on the Hauraki Gulf, chasing the work ups with the kids, a couple of mates, or a combination of the two. &nbsp;</p>','A',9,'1'),(62,'Paul','Yates','Corporate Team member','pauly@arht.org.nz','021 632453','09 9507265','','/library/support/paul-yates.jpg','','<p>Paul worked for 30 years in the Toy industry, starting with a Saturday morning job at the Toy Warehouse. He then progressed to management and became a Branch Manager for Deka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following on from Deka, Paul worked as an Account Manager at Thos Holdsworth &amp; Sons Ltd for 20 years before, joining ARHT in 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, Paul likes to ride his Harley Davidson Motorcycle as often as possible, and also enjoys a spot of fishing and mountain biking.</p>','A',22,'1'),(63,'Leanda','Hunt','TO BE CONFIRMED','','','','','','','','D',0,''),(64,'Nathan','Turley','Events Manager','nathant@arht.org.nz','021 339988','09 9507261','','/library/support/nathan-turley.jpg','','<p>Nathan has been with the Trust for over five years, and is in charge of our fundraising events portfolio.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The events team run various events throughout the year to suit many different types of interests and markets. Events play a vital role in our fundraising organisation, allowing us to connect with supporters in a unique and rewarding way. Since Nathan has been with the Trust we have added numerous new events to the fundraising calendar and run some iconic events throughout our region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nathan enjoys working with a fantastic fundraising team and especially achieving good outcomes for the service and community, whilst having a great time along the way.</p>','A',19,'1'),(65,'Jeff','Nother','I.T. Manager','it@arht.org.z','021 2748666','09 9507202','','/library/support/jeffnother.jpg','','<p>Jeff joined the Trust in early 1997 as the Database Coordinator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His involvement over the years with the development and administration of systems and fundraising projects has seen him progress to his current role of&nbsp; I.T. Manager.</p>','A',12,'1'),(66,'Leon','Ford','Crewman','','','','','/library/crewmen/leon-ford.jpg','','','H',2,''),(67,'Bruce','Kerr','Patient Liaison Officer','brucek@arht.org.nz','','09 9507264','','/library/support/bruce-at-his-desk.jpg','','<p>Bruce Kerr is an ex-Intensive Care Paramedic for the Trust. He retired from full-time active duty in December 2016, after over 20 years service with ARHT and 20 years with St John Ambulance. Bruce completed over 3,000 rescue missions in that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bruce is now working two days a week out of the Trust&#39;s fundraising office, speaking to our patients and answering any questions they may have, as well as assisting Kerrie (Planned Giving Manager) with bequest related enquiries and speaking engagements.</p>','A',11,'1'),(68,'Miles','Tillott','Community Team member','milest@arht.org.nz','','09 9507274','','/library/support/miles_pp_col_rs.jpg','','<p>Miles has been part of the Community Fundraising team for almost two years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Miles enjoys talking to all of the Trust&#39;s loyal supporters and says that&nbsp;being part of a world class rescue helicopter service is what keeps him going. That and a bit of golf or fishing at the weekend!</p>','A',17,'1'),(69,'Greg','Brownson','Helicopter Manager / Maintenance Controller','greg@arht.org.nz','','09 9507210','','/library/crewmen/browndog.jpg','','<p>Greg served in the NZ Army in Vietnam, 161 battery 1970-1971. He joined Red Beach Surf Club in 1979, gaining surf medallion and first aid and acting as powercraft officer and surf boat crewman.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1983 Greg joined the Helicopter Rescue Squad as a crewman. He then qualified as a NZUA Diver and Crewman instructor and in 1986 was Helicopter Crewman of the year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1991 Greg joined the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust as a fulltime Helicopter Rescue crewman instructor, HUET instructor and Sea Survival Instructor and become Crew Chief in 1992.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2000, after 17 years at the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust, Greg was appointed Helicopter Manager. Greg also has qualifications as instructor in Winch Training, Helicopter Underwater Escape Training and maintaining helicopter crews training standards. Greg is also a qualified Motor Mechanic.</p>','A',9,'1'),(70,'Barry','Watkin','Logistical Support','','','','','/library/support/barry-watkin.jpg','','<p>Barry was the Chief Paramedic for the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust, retiring from active duty in 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barry has worked for the rescue service since 1997 and now continues in a flexible part-time role, assisting with vehicle management, equipment pick-up, staff retrievals, public speaking engagements and ambulance liaison. He also provides helicopter awareness/safety presentations to rural Ambulance and/or NZ Fire service staff, as well as training and education for rural EMS volunteers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barry enjoys continuing to promote the Auckland Rescue Helicopter Trust in any capacity he can.</p>','A',21,''),(71,'Jane','Dyke','Quality Assurance Assistant','janed@arht.org.nz','','09 9507223','','/library/support/jane-dyke.jpg','','<p>Jane Dyke started working for the ARHT in 2013. Jane&#39;s role is to assist the Quality Manager, SMS Manager and Flight Operations Manager to maintain ARHT&#39;s documentation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In her spare time she enjoys exercise, travelling, the outdoors and being a joyologist :)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She also loves to spend time with her dog, who she gets to take kayaking and (hopefully soon) paddle-boarding too!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','A',4,'1'),(72,'Leanda','Hunt','PA to CEO & FOM','leanda@arht.org.nz','','09 9507209','','/library/support/leanda-hunt.jpg','','<p>Leanda began working for ARHT in 2015. Prior to that she was&nbsp;in a business advisory&nbsp;role for the Business Excellence Awards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','A',10,'1'),(73,'Lorraine','Patterson','Accounts','lorraine@arht.org.nz','','09 9507206','','/library/support/lorraine-patterson.jpg','','<p>Lorraine began working for ARHT in 2000.</p>','A',13,'1'),(74,'Gareth','Richards','HEMS Doctor','','','','','/library/hems-doctors/dr-gareth-richards.jpg','','','H',0,''),(75,'Stephanie','Valent','HEMS Fellow','','','','','','','','H',0,''),(76,'Scott','Orman','HEMS Doctor','','','','','','','<p>Scott is an emergency medicine specialist at Auckland Hospital. He lives in Auckland with his wife and three sons, and when not at work is usually found on or in the water.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scott has interests in patient safety and digital technology, and created the AucklandHEMS.com website and the Auckland HEMS smartphone app.</p>','H',0,''),(77,'Arthur','Brewer','Community Team','','','','','/library/support/arthur-brewer.jpg','','<p>Arthur joined ARHT in early June 2017.&nbsp; Previous to that, Arthur had been in a Community Fundraising position for over&nbsp;two years, after studying in Political Science at UTSA.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, he is a musician, golfer, and basketball player.</p>','A',23,''),(78,'Zach','Butler','Community Team','','','','','/library/support/zach-butler.jpg','','<p>Zach joined ARHT early this year, as a&nbsp; part-time Fundraiser, alongside studying towards his BCom at the University of Auckland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is super excited to be part of the team, and looking forward to making a difference with his role at ARHT.</p>','A',24,'');
